    <description>A war game set in Greg Stafford's world of Glorantha, wherein players move armies composed of the five tribes of Prax--the Bison, the Morokanth, the Sable, the Impala, and the Independents. The explanation of the game in the original rules describes it such: &amp;quot;This game is the second of an interlocking triad of fantasies which deal with various aspects of man's magic and his relationship with the gods and the unknown.&amp;quot; The first was White Bear &amp; Red Moon (republished and better known as Dragon Pass), while the third, Masters of Luck &amp;amp; Death, was never published.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Originally published by Chaosium in 1977, the game was massively revised for a French language release by Oriflam in 1994 as Les Dieux Nomades, which has a more solid game system and much higher quality components.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
